'''{{lang|fr|France Nature Environnement}}''' is the French federation of associations for the protection of nature and the environment.<ref>http://www.fne.asso.fr/fr/federation/presentation.html</ref> Created in 1968 as the ''{{lang|fr|Fédération française des sociétés de protection de la nature}}'' (French Federation of Societies for the Protection of Nature), it was recognised as being ''{{lang|fr|d'utilité publique}}'' (having public benefits) in 1976. It speaks on behalf of a movement of 3000 associations, grouped into 80 member organisations in France and its overseas territories. The logo of the Federation is the hedgehog, and its motto is ''{{lang|fr|Partout où la nature a besoin de nous}}'' ("Everywhere nature needs us").

