{{Infobox power station |name = Storrun Wind Farm |image = |image_caption = |country = [[Sweden]] |location = [[Krokom]], [[Jämtland]] |owner = Storrun Vindkraft AB |status = O |ps_units_operational= 12&nbsp;[[Nordex]] 2.5&nbsp;MW N90 |ps_electrical_capacity= 30&nbsp;MW |commissioned = 2009 |decommissioned = }} '''Storrun Wind Farm''' is a 30&nbsp;MW wind farm in [[Krokom]] in [[Jämtland]], [[Sweden]]. The wind farm was opened on 26 September 2009. It consists of 12&nbsp;[[Nordex]] 2.5&nbsp;MW N90 wind turbines.<ref name=oilvoice> {{cite news | url = http://www.oilvoice.com/n/DONG_Energy_Invests_in_Swedish_Wind_Farm/8b13ba5d.aspx | title = DONG Energy Invests in Swedish Wind Farm | publisher = OilVoice | date = 2008-02-08 | accessdate = 2008-06-24}} </ref> The developer and operator of the wind farm is Storrun Vindkraft AB, a joint venture of [[DONG Energy]] (80%) and [[Borevind]] AB (20%).<ref> {{cite paper |url=http://www.dongenergy.com/SiteCollectionDocuments/wind/Storrun/Datasheet_Storrun.pdf |title=Storrun |format=PDF |publisher=[[DONG Energy]] |accessdate= 2010-08-30}} </ref> The wind farm covers an area of approximately {{convert|2.6|km2}} and average wind speed at the {{convert|80|m}} hub height is {{convert|7.3|m/s}}. Due to the northern location, the project includes anti-ice coated blades and estimation of production losses caused by icing.
