{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}
'''Vankusawade Wind Park''' is a wind farm located on a high mountain plateau at 1,150 m above the [[Shivaji Lake|Koyana Reservoir]], around 40&nbsp;km from the town of [[Satara Town|Satara]], Satara District in [[Maharashtra]].<ref>http://www.suzlon.com/global_footprint.html</ref>

Wind power is generated from Suzlon S33/350 turbines of 350&nbsp;kW each, resulting in a total power output of 210 MW.<ref>{{cite web|title=Among the clouds|url=http://www.powertoday.in/News.aspx?nId=OqlYYE0cesCp9XfI6VCtIw==&NewsType=Among-the-clouds-India-Sector|website=Power Today|publisher=Power Today|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>

